olive oil
½ unit onion
2 clove garlic
½ sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend
1 punnet button mushrooms
20 g butter
8 unit Mini Flour Tortillas
1 block Cheddar cheese
½ tin sweetcorn
1 unit tomato
1 bunch spring onion
2 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
½ tin black beans

Preheat the oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Thinly slice the brown onion (see ingredients list). Finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). Thinly slice the mushrooms. Grate the Cheddar cheese. Drain and rinse the black beans (see ingredients list). Transfer the black beans to a medium bowl and roughly mash with a potato masher or fork.

In a medium frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add the garlic and Mexican Fiesta spice blend (see ingredients list) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the sliced mushrooms, butter and another drizzle of olive oil and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to the bowl with the black beans and stir to combine.

Lay 1/2 the mini flour tortillas (see ingredients list) over an oven tray lined with baking paper. Divide the mushroom & black bean mixture between the tortillas and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top with the remaining tortillas and press down gently with the spatula. Brush or spray the tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil and season with salt and pepper.

Bake the quesadillas until the cheese has melted and the tortillas are golden, 10-12 minutes.

While the quesadillas are baking, wash out the pan and return to a high heat. Drain the sweetcorn (see ingredients list). Add the corn kernels and cook until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are jumping out. Finely chop the tomato. Thinly slice the spring onion. In a medium bowl, combine the charred corn, tomato and spring onion. Add the vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil. Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Cut the cheesy mushroom & black bean quesadillas into quarters. Serve with the tomato & charred corn salsa and Greek yoghurt on the side.